narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I'd recommend it. Similar amount of work to L3 or L4. Speaking definitely improves because we speak only in spanish every day. two presentations help that out too. fair tests/quizzes.

If you really want to study Spanish farther, take it. If you have to take it for distributional requirements, take it. It is not too much work, and much less than the other Yale Spanish classes. You also don't really learn too many NEW grammar points.
It's a really interesting class in Spanish and well worth going beyond L3 for more credits
It is a good course, depending on your teacher. Some make class more fun than others. A little too much busy, mindless work...work book exercises.
I would recommend but not with Ricardo.
